&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;ONL Supports the [&lt;a href=&#34;http://www.edge-core.com/productsInfo.php?cls=1&amp;amp;cls2=7&amp;amp;cls3=57&amp;amp;id=110&#34;&gt;Wedge 40&lt;/a&gt;] running the Facebook [&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/facebook/fboss&#34;&gt;FBOSS&lt;/a&gt;] fowarding agent and [&lt;a href=&#34;http://www.snaproute.com/&#34;&gt;Snaproute&lt;/a&gt;].&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;ONL Supports the Wedge 100 running [&lt;a href=&#34;http://www.snaproute.com/&#34;&gt;Snaproute&lt;/a&gt;].&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;installation-instructions&#34;&gt;Installation Instructions&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;If your Wedge does not have ONIE, you will need to install it to install ONL, it can be download from here:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Wedge 40 - &lt;a href=&#34;http://opennetlinux.org/binaries/accton-wedge/onie-recovery-wedge.iso&#34;&gt;ONIE for Wedge 40&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Wedge 100 - &lt;a href=&#34;http://opennetlinux.org/binaries/accton-wedge/onie-recovery-x86-64-facebook-wedge100-r0.iso&#34;&gt;ONIE for Wedge 100&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;Burn the ONIE .iso to a USB&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;Assuming that your USB is /dev/sdb, under linux you would do: dd if=onie-recovery-x86_64-accton_wedge_x16-r0.iso of=/dev/sdb bs=10M&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;Follow the directions in &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/opencomputeproject/OpenNetworkLinux/blob/master/docs/GettingStartedWedge.md&#34;&gt;Wedge Installation Guide&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

